snippet.textDisplay: Having a burger at least once a week is not a problem. That’s like me saying having any kind of food, like pizza or Mac n cheese, at least once a week is a  problem. It’s important to look at food neutrally instead of creating judgements that can hinder your body getting the nutrition it needs. Your body doesn’t see a burger from a fast food restaurant. It sees carbohydrates, protein, and fat, which are essential to the functioning of your body’s organs and cells. Furthermore, late night cravings come from your body saying you didn’t feed me what I needed during the day and I’m still hungry. If your body is hungry, you need to eat something. If you continue to ignore your body when it’s hungry, you could disrupt your body’s natural hunger and fullness cues, as well as your metabolism.
